UBA Signs $100 Million Deal With HSBC to Fund Imports

-- B y   P a u l   O k o l o
-- 
2011-03-01T08:44:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/united-bank-for-africa-gets-100-million-loan-from-hsbc.html
(Corrects to say the amount is a credit facility in story
that ran Feb. 28.)    United Bank for Africa Plc  of  Nigeria  signed an agreement with London-based  HSBC Holdings Plc 
to provide a $100 million, multi-currency standby credit
facility to its customers in 18 African countries for the
importation of goods, the Lagos-based lender said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Okolo in Abuja at 
 pokolo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
